Her arrival marks the third successful gorilla birth at the zoo. Bolingo, the suspected sire, was the park’s first gorilla birth in 2005. 

The mother, Mary, came to Busch Gardens in February 2010 from Gladys Porter Zoo in Brownsville, Texas, with her first daughter Pele, who just gave birth this past December to baby Enzi.

There are now seven gorillas in Busch Gardens' troop. 

Guests will be able to see the recently expanded clan on the Myombe Reserve habitat over the coming days.

The new addition is part of Busch Gardens’ participation in the Association of Zoos and Aquariums’ (AZA) Species Survival Plan (SSP).

